1.0:İnitial stage

1.1:İmplemented e-mail verification on backend and frontend.
    
    When users register for the first time they get an email contains email-verification-token.
    
    İf users are not verified and try open homepage they get a message navigates them to the "/verify-email" page and says "You are not verifed. Please verify your account".

    In "/verify-email" page users can verify their e-mail by using verification token that sent to their e-mails.

    After a day when users verification token has been sent to the users' email, verification token expires and users can no longer use their tokens for verify their emails.

    If verification token expires users can access their new tokens by pressing "Resend" button.

    After user is verified they can no longer acces "/verify-email" page.


